HEADWORD: Ceroon
<hw>Ce*roon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Seroon</er>.]</ety> <def>A bale or package. covered with hide, or
with wood bound with hide; <as>as, a <ex>ceroon</ex> of indigo,
cochineal, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ceroplastic</ent>⟦br⟧
